           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I started a necro last night to play with two of my friends who created mages recently. I dropped 5k on him to start with, my magelo is <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=710575" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=710575</a><br /><br />I'm taking a break from my main, a 65 monk. From some initial browsing it seems the consensus is get your int over 200, and then focus on hp gear. If anyone could provide some insight into what gear to get, that would be great. I have another 6k to spend, and if it was worthwhile could raise another 15-20 on top of that. The cloak is on loan from my main, and he also has a hammered golden hoop (75hp's, 8 sta, neg15AC) which I could use on my necro if you think its worthwhile? If i'm not wrong, the reason the emphasis is placed on hp's is due to the hp's to mana spells. So if someone could provide some gear advice, that would be great.<br /><br />I also have a few questions I'd be very greatful if someone could answer them.<br /><br />1. Which focus effects are worthwhile for a necro?<br /><br />2. How much mana does 1 int yeild, above and below 200 int?<br /><br />3. Does fd's failure rate decrease as the abjuration skill increases?<br /><br />4. Are there any items that really make a huge difference? (like the fungi for monks and other melee)<br /><br />Thanks a lot in advance.</span id="msg"></font>
