                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Advice on getting int to 200 first is wrong, in my opinion.  As a necro, you will be meleeing into your low 30s (because of your strategy in zones you'll be hunting, and getting defense maxed), so low level necros should go for HP first.  Only bother with raising int much if you are a twink (which you are), or after level 30.<br /><br />You want affliction haste and affliction efficiency.  Once you have those, consider extended range (important later), mana preservation and spell haste.<br /><br />At 60, 1 int = 12 mana; over 200, 1 int = 6 mana.  At lower levels, this amount is correspondingly less.<br /><br />FD fizzles less if abjuration is higher.  Fail rate seems to be random.  Get used to spell FD being much worse than monk FD.<br /><br />Regen items rule - both for melee, same as monks, but also once you start to get decent lich spells, really from Call of Bones (34) upwards.<br /><br />Also see <a href="http://www.paullynch.org/cgi-bin/blosxom/Everquest/necro_twink.story" target="_blank">http://www.paullynch.org/cgi-bin/blosxom/Everquest/necro_twink.story</a> and Deedrok's Guide to Twinking <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=646078." target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=646078.</a></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
